.Dd 
.Dt STRRCHR 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm strrchr
.Nd locate character in string
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <string.h>
.Ft char *
.Fn strrchr "const char *s" "int c"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn strrchr
function
locates the last occurrence of
.Fa c
(converted to a char)
in the string
.Fa s .
If
.Fa c
is
.Ql \e0 ,
.Fn strrchr
locates the terminating
.Ql \e0 .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Fn strrchr
function
returns a pointer to the character,
or a null
pointer if
.Fa c
does not occur anywhere in
.Fa s .
